      "claim": "The reaction is zero order in NH3 ($\\text{rate} = k$) — an experimentally determined rate law that holds while the tungsten surface is saturated, not read off the balanced equation. The order and rate constant $k$ are the sourced data; the integrated law and half-life follow exactly.",
      "kind": "model"
    },
    {
      "claim": "The zero-order regime holds throughout the run modeled here — fixed temperature, the surface kept saturated — so the straight-line decay applies until the ammonia is nearly gone (at very low [NH3] the surface is no longer saturated and the true order changes).",
